<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="1" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1982,2008]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,393]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="1" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,258,1982,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="43">Remarks</emphasis>
. The type species was described from 
<specimenCount box="[706,835,1982,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="43" type="male">three males</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[845,940,1982,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="43">syntypes</typeStatus>
from Elisabethville (currently Lubumbashi, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,209,151,177]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">DRC</collectingCountry>
) (ex-coll. Seydel). The examination of the type series, deposited in RMCA, shows that the genus is actually very close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1886" box="[242,354,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Charltona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[242,354,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Charltona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male genitalia differ in the strong development of the vinculum and in the phallus subapically broadened, as opposed to the moderate development of the vinculum and cylindrical phallus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1886" box="[1198,1310,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Charltona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1198,1310,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Charltona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1886" box="[293,405,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Charltona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,405,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Charltona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including examination of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1933" box="[696,939,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Cypholomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptodeta">
<emphasis box="[696,939,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Cypholomia leptodeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed in order to ascertain the validity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1933" box="[151,285,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Cypholomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,285,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Cypholomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[299,472,295,321]" firstAuthor="Meyrick" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" refId="ref10901" refString="Meyrick, E. (1930 - 1936) Exotic Microlepidoptera. Taylor and Francis, London, 642 pp." type="book" year="1930">Meyrick (1934)</bibRefCitation>
described two additional species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1933" box="[871,1005,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Cypholomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[871,1005,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Cypholomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1934" box="[1019,1169,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Cypholomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amphiaula">
<emphasis box="[1019,1169,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">C. amphiaula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1934" box="[1223,1368,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Cypholomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crypsibela">
<emphasis box="[1223,1368,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">C. crypsibela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both have genitalia structure rather different from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1933" box="[713,845,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Cypholomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptodeta">
<emphasis box="[713,845,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">C. leptodeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and are respectively transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bassi &amp; Poltavsky" authorityName="Bassi &amp; Poltavsky" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Ancylogastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1225,1371,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Ancylogastra</emphasis>
Bassi &amp; Poltavsky
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[298,374,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[298,374,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[427,549,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Prionotalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[427,549,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Prionotalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, below.
</paragraph>
